law.text:
The department may revoke or suspend any plumber's license issued by it upon proof that the licensee has:
Knowingly violated the provisions of this chapter or the Kentucky State Plumbing Code, or the rules and regulations of the department;
Practiced fraud or deception in applying for or obtaining a license;
Is incompetent to perform services as a licensed master plumber or a licensed journeyman plumber;
Permitted his or her license to be used directly or indirectly by another to obtain or perform plumbing work or services; or
Is guilty of such other unprofessional or dishonorable conduct of a character likely to deceive or defraud the public.
